content:
Yes, the minimum value of the objective function that Excel found (-0.5202) is the minimum value of the function over the feasible region defined by the constraint.

In the earlier messages, I provided you with the optimal coordinates (x1, x2) where the minimum value of the function is attained, as well as the optimal Lagrange multiplier. These coordinates can be used to verify the solution that Excel found, as well as to get a better understanding of the location of the minimum point and the behavior of the function in the neighborhood of that point.

The optimal coordinates are not necessary to answer the original question of finding the minimum value of the function, but they can provide additional insight into the optimization problem.
